<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>Ali Oetjen recently poured her heart out on social media over her split with boyfriend Taite Radley.</p>

<p>And on Thursday, the blonde beauty, 34, retreated to the gym to focus on getting her body into peak form.</p>

<p>She shared a photo of herself doing a pull-up on a bar, an exercise that brought out her impressive back muscles.</p>

<p>Wow! On Thursday, former Bachelorette star Ali Oetjen (pictured) hit the gym and showed off her impressive back muscles as she does a pull-up. In the caption she said: 'Feeling strong physically, but my mental and emotional strength has been compromised'</p>

<p>In the caption, the former Bachelorette, who is known for her very healthy and active lifestyle, said: 'Feeling strong physically, but my mental and emotional strength has been compromised.'</p>

<p>She then thanked her legions of fans for the advice and recommendations for their wise words and inspiration quotes.</p>

<p>Ali shared a list of activities she's been working on to keep busy with including yoga, meditation, a 2021 goal list - including creating her own protein bar - as well as journaling.</p>

<p>Busy: Ali shared a list of activities she's been working on to keep busy with including yoga, meditation, a 2021 goal list - including creating her own protein bar - as well as journaling</p>

<p>She also revealed that she has given up alcohol since March, saying: 'Easy, this is going to make me so much more upset and feel horrible &amp; lonely the next day. </p>

<p>'Haven't drunk since March,' she added. </p>

<p>Recentlt, Ali broke down in tears in an emotional video about moving on from her ex boyfriend Taite Radley, following their split back in July.</p>

<p>Still heart broken: Recently, Ali broke down in tears in an emotional video about moving on from her ex boyfriend Taite Radley, following their split back in July</p>

<p>Brave: Ali admitted that she 'still loves' her ex - but that she 'knows we don't align'</p>

<p>The footage shows the devastated blonde wiping tears from her mascara-stained eyes and admitted that she 'still loves' her ex - but that she 'knows we don't align'.</p>

<p>'It's bloody slow healing, sadness &amp; hurt fill my whole body. </p>

<p>'Meditation, Yoga, exercise, nature, cooking, family, friends and focusing on my goals allows for my peaceful spirit to just be. </p>

<p>Over: Ali and Taite (left) had been separated for 88 days prior to their split due to the coronavirus pandemic - said that they were 'taking time apart' </p>

<p>'I've never experienced anything like this where my soul still feels connected, I still love but know we don't align.' </p>

<p>The pair - who had been separated for 88 days prior to their split due to the coronavirus pandemic - said that they were 'taking time apart' and giving each other 'some space'.</p>

<p>The former couple, who met on The Bachelorette in 2018, said that they still loved each other and didn't rule out a possible reconciliation. </p>

